I'm still a newbie when it comes to audio engineering, but I've found from simple observation, that there's a huge difference between varying qualities of the same track.
M a n B i r d ‚Ñ¢ 2024-01-29 4:26 AM
in the case of digital files what you wanna look for is sample rate, so like mp3 files usually go up to 320 kpbs, but some other file types go in the thousands, you can hear the difference with those mostly in the top end and clarity when lots of things are happening at once. so in higher quality files the top end is cleaner / clearer and the clarity between instruments and layers is much better, it can take some getting used to for identifying these things but even when you dont really know what it is, many ppl will be able to tell some difference between files on nice playback devices
1
4:27 AM
